# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
!framework/workflows/runbooks/build/
!workflows/runbooks/build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
env/

# Runtime state
.session-buffer/
*.log

# Workflow-engine process-lock (0-byte mutex, machine-local — content
# files .workflow-state/*.json + archive/ are TRACKED for laptop-hop
# survival; see framework/workflow-engine-cookbook.md §Multi-machine).
.workflow-state/_lock

# Sub-agent observability output (transient, per-run)
workspace/

# Build / generator output (ephemeral, regenerated via scripts/generate-*.py + deploy-docs.sh)
_site/

# Session-handoff .bak safety copy (save/quicksave writes this before overwrite)
# save/WORKFLOW.md Step 4 schreibt <path>.bak ohne leading dot — beide Varianten abfangen.
.session-handoff.md.bak
.session-handoff-*.md.bak
session-handoff.md.bak
session-handoff-*.md.bak
context/session-handoff.md.bak
context/session-handoff-*.md.bak

# Local CC overrides
.claude/settings.local.json

# User-specific generated configs (Templates: *.example.jsonc/*.example.txt)
orchestrators/opencode/opencode.jsonc
.claude/path-whitelist.txt

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~
launch/

# Session-state (operational, not for public-repo)
context/session-handoff.md
context/session-handoff*.md.bak
context/session-log.md
context/history/*.md

# Internal review-process artefacts (board reviews, adversary outputs, audits)
# These are operational discipline-tools, not framework-content. Public repo
# stays framework-only.
docs/reviews/
docs/audits/
docs/audit/

# Internal scoping/research artefacts (one-off documents, not framework-content)
research.md
docs/research/

# Internal workflow-state files (per-session audit trail, not framework-content)
# These mirror the workflow_engine state but in human-readable form.
# Convention: singular per workflow-name (docs/<workflow>/).
docs/build/
docs/solve/
docs/fix/
docs/review/
docs/docs-rewrite/

# Internal spec-drafts (intermediate edit-plans + transient specs from solve/build)
# Specs that are framework-relevant move to a tracked location explicitly.
docs/specs/

# Internal handover-bundles (cross-repo handoffs, dogfooding-reports)
docs/handovers/

# Internal cross-repo discovery logs — TRACKED (not gitignored).
# Pre-OSS-Squash 2026-05-04: this dir was gitignored, content lost in
# 14f8fab squash (recovered via dangling-commit 681ac03). Removed-from-
# gitignore so engineering substance persists across future squashes.
# Future OSS-prep: exclude via squash-config or branch-strategy, not
# .gitignore. See docs/discoveries/README.md for policy.
# docs/discoveries/  ← intentionally NOT ignored anymore

# Auxiliary task-files (per-task audit trail: gates, delegation, test-plan)
# Tasks themselves stay tracked under docs/tasks/<NNN>.{md,yaml}.
# Auxiliary files are operational state, not historical work-record.
docs/tasks/*-gates.yaml
docs/tasks/*-gates.md
docs/tasks/*-delegation.md
docs/tasks/*-delegation.yaml
docs/tasks/*-test-plan.md
docs/tasks/*-test-plan.yaml

# Scheduled-task lock (CC scheduling, runtime-only)
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# Hook + agent runtime state (per-machine, ephemeral)
.claude/state/

# Session-runtime markers (board-runs, plan-adversary, ephemeral)
.session/
